                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12735361" author="elman" created="Sun, 26 Jul 2009 08:23:34 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is patch by Nadav Fischer. Assigning issue to Nadav.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12735365" author="nfischer" created="Sun, 26 Jul 2009 08:53:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;should this be handled for 0.1 or can it wait for 0.2?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12735714" author="bluk" created="Mon, 27 Jul 2009 19:02:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think if we already have a simple solution that we should just go ahead and apply it to trunk.  The code will eventually be changed to fix the issue so if the solution is good enough today, why not?  It would give users more assurance that there are fewer open issues and they would be using what the code looks like eventually anyway.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12735970" author="nfischer" created="Tue, 28 Jul 2009 07:44:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The fix also allows for sub-resource locators to specify an empty path, something like:&lt;/p&gt;


&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;@Path(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hello&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Resource {
    @GET
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; getHello() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Hello&quot;&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
        
    @Path(&quot;&quot;)
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; Located locator() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Located();
    }
}

&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;static&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Located {
    @GET
    @Path(&lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;world&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;public&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;String&lt;/span&gt; getHelloWorld() {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Hello world&quot;&lt;/span&gt;;
    }
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So that a request to /hello will yield &quot;Hello&quot; and a request to /hello/world will yield &quot;Hello world&quot;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12736598" author="hudson" created="Wed, 29 Jul 2009 12:12:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Integrated in Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5 #50 (See &lt;a href=&quot;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/50/&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://hudson.zones.apache.org/hudson/job/Wink-Trunk-JDK1.5/50/&lt;/a&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;
</comment>
                            <comment id="12739557" author="bluk" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2009 15:11:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Looks good.  Thanks Nadav.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
